==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bumpkin
<hw>Bump"kin</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[The same word as
<ets>bumkin</ets>, which Cotgrave defines thus:
⟦ldquo⟧<ets>Bumkin</ets>, Fr. chicambault, the luffe-block, a long and
thick piece of wood, whereunto the fore-sayle and sprit-sayle are
fastened, when a ship goes by the winde.⟦rdquo⟧ Hence, a clumsy man may
easily have been compared to such a block of wood; cf. OD.
<ets>boomken</ets> a little tree. See <er>Boom</er> a pole.]</ety>
<def>An awkward, heavy country fellow; a clown; a country lout.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧Bashful country <xex>bumpkins</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>W.
Irving.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>bumpkinly</ent>⟦br⟧
